					<description><![CDATA[<p>Cowboy Space Corporation has just completed a $275 million Series B funding round. The funding values the firm at $2 billion, marking a major pivot and rebrand from its previous</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cowboy-space-corporation-raises-275m-in-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cowboy Space Corporation Raises $275M in Funding Round</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://ventureburn.com/capital-b-raises-17-8m-bitcoin-treasury-expansion/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cowboy Space Corporation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has just completed a $275 million Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/capital-b-raises-17-8m-bitcoin-treasury-expansion/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. </span>The funding values the firm at $2 billion, marking a major pivot and rebrand from its previous name, Aetherflux. Index Ventures led the round, with IVP, Blossom Capital, SAIC, Breakthrough Energy Ventures, and Andreessen Horowitz participating. The capital aims to build vertically integrated infrastructure, combining launch vehicles with orbital data centres for AI compute demand.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Vision: AI in the High Frontier</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Baiju Bhatt, the billionaire co-founder of Robinhood, Cowboy Space Corporation is moving beyond its original mission of space-based solar power. While the company still intends to utilise solar energy, its primary focus has shifted to solving a terrestrial problem: the staggering energy and space requirements of AI data centres.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201006" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201006" class="size-full wp-image-201006" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Cowboy-Space-Corporation.jpg" alt="Cowboy Space Corporation" width="480" height="80" /><p id="caption-attachment-201006" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Cowboy Space Corporation</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are building for a future where the demand for AI compute and energy begins to outstrip what Earth’s infrastructure can support,&#8221; said Bhatt, who serves as CEO. &#8220;Our approach starts from a blank sheet. We aren&#8217;t just putting servers on a satellite; we are designing the rocket and the data centre as a single, unified system.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/capital-b-raises-17-8m-bitcoin-treasury-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Capital B Raises $17.8M To Expand Bitcoin Treasury Holdings</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Engineering a One-Megawatt Data Center</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The core of Cowboy’s strategy is its proprietary launch vehicle. Unlike traditional rockets that deploy a separate payload and discard the upper stage, Cowboy’s rocket is designed so the upper stage remains in orbit, transforming into a one-megawatt operational data centre.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This unified architecture eliminates redundant mass and optimises power delivery. To achieve the high-performance computing required for AI, Cowboy is collaborating with NVIDIA to deploy the newly announced NVIDIA Space-1 Vera Rubin Modules. These modules are specifically hardened for the harsh environment of space, allowing for real-time AI inference and data processing directly in Low Earth Orbit (LEO).</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rebranding to Cowboy</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The transition from the ethereal &#8220;Aetherflux&#8221; to the rugged &#8220;Cowboy Space Corporation&#8221; reflects Bhatt’s desire to capture a more adventurous, trail-blazing spirit. The company’s new mission statement, &#8220;Powering humanity from the high frontier&#8221;, leans heavily into the Western-themed aesthetic of exploration and independence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;The name captures the scale of our ambition,&#8221; Bhatt told reporters. &#8220;We are blazing our own trail in space, building the critical pieces of the infrastructure stack that we need to own to control the economics of the future.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">What’s Next for the High Frontier?</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is moving at a breakneck pace. </span>Cowboy Space will launch its first test satellite later this year to demonstrate its space-to-Earth power beaming system. The first launch of the integrated rocket and data centre will only be in late 2028.</p>
<p>Cowboy Space Corporation&#8217;s team comprises veterans from SpaceX, NASA, and NVIDIA. The company is positioned at the intersection of two capital-intensive industries: aerospace and artificial intelligence. If successful, the company won&#8217;t just be launching rockets; it will be launching the first truly extraterrestrial industrial backbone.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cowboy-space-corporation-raises-275m-in-funding-round/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cowboy Space Corporation Raises $275M in Funding Round</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
