					<description><![CDATA[<p>Grand Games has raised a $70 million Series B funding round. The investment, led by Balderton Capital, arrives just over a year after the company’s Series A, signalling an extraordinary</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/grand-games-secures-70m-to-expand-mobile-gaming-studio/" data-wpel-link="internal">Grand Games Secures $70M to Expand Mobile Gaming Studio</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://grand.gs/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Grand Games</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has raised a $70 million Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/procurepro-raises-11m-for-ai-construction-procurement/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The investment, led by Balderton Capital, arrives just over a year after the company’s Series A, signalling an extraordinary growth trajectory for the two-year-old startup.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round saw strong participation from existing backers, including Bek Ventures and Laton Ventures, alongside high-profile angel investor Mert Gür. This latest injection brings Grand Games’ total capital raised to $103 million since its founding in early 2024, reportedly pushing the company’s valuation to a nearly sixfold increase in just 12 months.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A New Standard for Hybrid-Casual</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Grand Games has established a clear leadership position in this hybrid-casual space. This is an emerging genre that combines the light, click-to-play gameplay of hypercasuals with the retention &amp; monetisation demanded in midcore offerings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s most popular hits, </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Magic Sort</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400"> and </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Block Out</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400">, recently hit numbers 1 &amp; 2 on the US iOS most-downloaded games list. Other hits have accumulated more than 50 million downloads in over 200 countries, on the strength of the company&#8217;s ability to use data to create the perfect puzzle mechanics.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201002" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201002" class="size-large wp-image-201002" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Person-playing-computer-games-1024x683.jpg" alt="Person playing computer games" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-201002" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We started Grand to build the kind of company we believed could unlock the full potential of great talent,&#8221; said Bekir Batuhan Çelebi, CEO and co-founder of Grand Games. &#8220;Türkiye has produced some of the best mobile gaming talent in the world, and we wanted to create an environment where that talent has real ownership over decisions, product direction, and outcomes.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/procurepro-raises-11m-for-ai-construction-procurement/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">ProcurePro Raises $11M for AI Construction Procurement</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Empowering the Multi-Studio Model</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike traditional top-down development houses, Grand Games employs a multi-studio approach. The company, which is currently made up of five independent studios working in parallel, is structured internally in a way that allows its team of 75 people to test, iterate, and release a game faster than many much larger opponents.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $70 million in fresh capital is earmarked for three primary pillars of expansion:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Aggressive Marketing:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Scaling user acquisition for current chart-toppers to maintain their global rankings.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Pipeline Acceleration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Funding the development of a strong pipeline of upcoming releases in the pouring-puzzle and car-customisation genres.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Talent Acquisition:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Continuing a hiring spree to bring in top-tier engineering and creative talent within the Istanbul tech hub.</span></li>
</ol>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Investor Verdict</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Balderton Capital, which doubled down on its initial investment from 2025, highlighted the team’s exceptional execution as the primary reason for the large check. &#8220;Grand is unquestionably one of the most exceptional teams in this category,&#8221; said Rana Yared, Partner at Balderton. &#8220;Our conviction in what Batu, Mehmet, Mustafa, and the team are building is stronger than ever.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to industry analysts, Grand Games is strongly heading towards unicorn status ($1bn valuation). Thanks to its recurring growth of fivefold, the Dutch studio is taking advantage of a healthy domestic ecosystem: Turks, the company launched in, and the government recently announced that it would subsidise by half the cost for mobile game development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With the mobile gaming industry becoming more and more saturated, the combination of the fast-going nature of the market and the company&#8217;s superior delivery seems to indicate that perhaps the next big developer in this industry will not be based in Silicon Valley; instead, one day it might be based on the shores of the Bosphorus.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/grand-games-secures-70m-to-expand-mobile-gaming-studio/" data-wpel-link="internal">Grand Games Secures $70M to Expand Mobile Gaming Studio</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
